Regardless of the errors, Deagan and Cruxent have accomplished their goal of reaching multiple audi­ences. Columbus's Outpost stands alone, both in the sense that it can be understood by the nonspecialist without Archaeology at La /sabela and, I would argue, in quality comparisons to historical texts about the time period in general. Its companion volume elabo­rates nicely on a number of issues and contains signif­icant evidence that is relevant to professionals in the area. Anyone curious about America's colonial past should read the accessible Columbus's Outpost; those with a specialized interest would benefit greatly from having this comprehensive set of texts in their library. 
